OL,3,CThe new service that's helping cancer
OL,4,Cpatients and reducing A&E pressures
OL,6,FNow, if her immunotherapy makes her
OL,7,Funwell, Sharon has access to on-day
OL,8,Fspecialised emergency treatment. It
OL,9,Fmeans she no longer has to go through
OL,10,Fthe complex process of receiving
OL,11,Ftreatments at A&E departments.
OL,13,FSharon continued: "I phoned the
OL,14,Fhelpline and they got back to me then
OL,15,Fwithin 20 minutes telling me what to
OL,16,Fdo - to come into Velindre and they
OL,17,Fput me on a drip of steroids."
OL,19,FImmunotherapy is a treatment that uses
OL,20,Fthe body's own immune system to
OL,21,Frecognise and destroy cancer.
